Content:
Trivially little compared to the code base and compared to the advantages. It takes only a few seconds to type<p><pre><code>  if (object == null)
  {
    throw new IllegalArgumentException("Parameter 'object' should not be null.");
  }
</code></pre>
Whereas I could lose hours chasing after null values that were passed through layers of unguarded abstractions.<p>Sure, I'd love for DBC to be a language feature (Eiffel has it) but exceptions help me out here, too.
